1
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:41,133
<i> We should call dad.</i>

2
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> Hazel called me.</i>

3
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,567
<i>She forbade me from talking
to your dad.</i>

4
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,933
<i>Manuel, let me manage
your salary.</i>

5
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,633
<i>You don't need to take
his money.</i>

6
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:51,667
<i>As long as he is supporting
them,</i>

7
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:54,300
<i>he won't cut communication
with Felma.</i>

8
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:55,433
<i> Andrea!</i>

9
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:58,200
<i>Why didn't you tell me
that you have an exam?</i>

10
00:00:58,333 --> 00:01:00,400
<i>I could have taken care
of your sister.</i>

11
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:01,867
<i> How are you going to do that</i>

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>when you're always tired
and drunk?</i>

13
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,267
<i> Dad.</i>

14
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,767
<i> Andrea, why are you crying?</i>

15
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,900
<i> I miss you so much.</i>

16
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,567
<i>Who are you talking to?
You're talking to your dad?</i>

17
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,600
<i>Didn't I tell you
not to call him anymore?</i>

18
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:13,667
<i> Mom! Give that back!</i>

19
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:14,733
<i> Hello?</i>

20
00:01:14,867 --> 00:01:16,600
<i>What if his wife answers
the phone?</i>

21
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:19,033
<i> Please spare me my dignity!</i>

22
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:30,533
Did you call Felma?

23
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,167
What?

24
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,567
Did you tell them
not to call me?

25
00:01:38,667 --> 00:01:40,333
Manuel, what are you
talking about?

26
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:42,233
Answer me!

27
00:01:48,633 --> 00:01:50,867
Yes, I forbade them
from calling you.

28
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:53,600
Why did you do that?

29
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:55,433
Do you really want to know?

30
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:58,000
How many times
have I told you

31
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:01,967
to prioritize me and our baby?
No one else.

32
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:05,667
How many times have I told you
that they're my family, too?

33
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,967
Can't I have them in my life,
too?

34
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,067
No way!

35
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,500
Manuel...

36
00:02:12,467 --> 00:02:13,833
we're doing fine without them.

37
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:18,500
We're doing okay when you're not
communicating with them.

38
00:02:19,767 --> 00:02:21,800
We're happy.

39
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:24,100
Our relationship
is going well.

40
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:28,233
But what about them?

41
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:29,933
Don't you think about
the consequences?

42
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:32,900
Andrea called me. She's crying.

43
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,000
Felma doesn't want them
to talk to me.

44
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:37,133
I don't understand
what's going on!

45
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,167
Felma's a grown woman.

46
00:02:42,367 --> 00:02:43,567
She can take care
of her children.

47
00:02:44,667 --> 00:02:45,633
And...

48
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,133
they're used
to not having you around.

49
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:53,933
But what about their needs?

50
00:02:56,233 --> 00:02:59,133
Hazel, why did you meddle again?

51
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:00,367
I thought you'd changed!

52
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,967
I thought you understood
my situation!

53
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,733
Manuel...

54
00:03:05,867 --> 00:03:06,833
Manuel, please.

55
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:10,567
Did you forget
what the doctor advised?

56
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,467
You know...

57
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,200
I can't get stressed.

58
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:15,500
Think about our baby.

59
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:16,900
You're right.

60
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:19,600
I'll just leave,
so you won't get stressed.

61
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:20,600
What?

62
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,233
What?

63
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:25,400
Wait, where are you going?

64
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:26,867
Wait!

65
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,800
Why?

66
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:29,333
Manuel!

67
00:03:29,467 --> 00:03:31,600
Wait! What are you doing?

68
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:32,633
Why are you packing your stuff?

69
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:33,833
- Leave me be!
- No!

70
00:03:33,967 --> 00:03:35,533
Wait!

71
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:36,967
Manuel!

72
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,200
Manuel, don't leave us.

73
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:40,900
Come on, you can't leave!

74
00:03:41,033 --> 00:03:43,233
I'm doing this for the baby.

75
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:47,133
Because whenever I'm here,
we do nothing but argue!

76
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,667
Manuel, you can't leave!

77
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,667
Wait, Manuel, please!

78
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,867
Wait.

79
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,767
- No, wait.
- Please, don't do this to me.

80
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:56,433
Wait, please.
Have some mercy, Manuel.

81
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:58,933
You can't do this.

82
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:00,900
You can't leave.

83
00:04:01,033 --> 00:04:02,433
What about our baby?

84
00:04:02,567 --> 00:04:05,167
You're going to leave me here
alone?

85
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,633
How am I going to cope?
I'm pregnant, Manuel.

86
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:08,833
- Let go of me!
- You can't leave me.

87
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:10,033
Manuel!

88
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:13,200
Manuel!

89
00:04:42,133 --> 00:04:43,933
<i> So what if I'm drunk?</i>

90
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:45,433
<i> I don't love Hazel.</i>

91
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:47,267
<i>You're the one I love,
you know that!</i>

92
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,667
<i> I'm just drunk.</i>

93
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:52,367
<i> I'm not stupid!</i>

94
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:55,033
<i> You won't marry that woman</i>

95
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:59,200
<i>if you don't feel
anything for her!</i>

96
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:01,067
<i> I'm the legal Mrs. Cruz now.</i>

97
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:03,000
<i>And you, you're a thing
of the past.</i>

98
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:07,100
<i>So if you keep bothering us,
what should I call you?</i>

99
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:08,033
<i> His mistress?</i>

100
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:09,567
<i> I'm not a mistress!</i>

101
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,800
<i> I'm the first wife!</i>

102
00:05:11,933 --> 00:05:12,900
<i> My children and I</i>

103
00:05:13,033 --> 00:05:15,233
<i>were Manuel's family
before you came along.</i>

104
00:05:15,367 --> 00:05:17,467
<i> Oh well, he married me!</i>

105
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,600
<i>So my baby and I
are his legal family.</i>

106
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:25,133
What kind of love are you
talking about, Manuel?

107
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:31,600
You can't even fight for me!

108
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,067
You bastard!

109
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:08,000
Get out of that car!

110
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:10,767
Hey, Miss!

111
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,567
What are you doing?

112
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:21,133
Get out of that car!

113
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:23,767
Hey! Miss!

114
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:25,933
What are you doing?

115
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,233
You're the one who ran me over,

116
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:30,667
and you have the guts
to act all arrogant.

117
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,633
You were crossing the road
without looking first!

118
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:37,067
Wait a minute...

119
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,167
are you drunk?

120
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,400
What do you care?
It's none of your business!

121
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,500
What do you mean
it's not my business?

122
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:42,933
You scratched my car!

123
00:06:43,067 --> 00:06:45,000
You're more concerned
about the scratch on your car

124
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,267
than my life!

125
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,100
- This is what you deserve!
- Hey!

126
00:06:48,233 --> 00:06:49,533
What the hell are you doing?

127
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:50,633
What the heck!

128
00:06:55,433 --> 00:06:56,233
Jeffrey.

129
00:06:58,633 --> 00:07:01,433
We need money for the
electricity and water bills.

130
00:07:01,567 --> 00:07:03,267
You have to tell mom.

131
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,567
She's still mad at me, remember?

132
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:10,867
Because you keep calling dad
when she told you not to.

133
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,133
But, Jeffrey...

134
00:07:13,267 --> 00:07:15,767
it's because I miss my dad.
How about you?

135
00:07:15,933 --> 00:07:17,267
Don't you miss him?

136
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,700
I miss him!

137
00:07:19,133 --> 00:07:20,800
But he's not coming back.

138
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:26,333
<i> Felma.</i>

139
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:28,733
- Someone's knocking.
- I'm coming.

140
00:07:34,633 --> 00:07:37,100
- Come in.
- Where's your mom?

141
00:07:37,467 --> 00:07:41,733
I'm here to pick up the sausage.
I ordered one kilo.

142
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:43,300
Wait, I'll get it for you.

143
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,400
Hello, Miss Lin.

144
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,667
Good day.

145
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:56,933
Miss Lin...

146
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:59,100
I'm sorry for the trouble.

147
00:07:59,233 --> 00:08:01,733
My mom hasn't made
the sausage yet.

148
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:02,967
What the heck.

149
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:05,433
I made the order a few days ago.

150
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:07,833
It was supposed to be delivered
yesterday.

151
00:08:07,967 --> 00:08:09,867
But she didn't show up.

152
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,233
I already paid for it.

153
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:13,467
Just give me a refund, then.

154
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,267
Miss Lin...

155
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,300
I'm sorry, but mom
didn't leave us the money.

156
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:21,133
What's going on with your mom?

157
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:23,400
She's being irresponsible.

158
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:25,267
It's so unlike her!

159
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:30,000
Tell her to give me my money
back, I'll come back tomorrow.

160
00:08:30,133 --> 00:08:32,167
I won't order from her
ever again!

161
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:33,400
I'm sorry, Miss Lin.

162
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,467
Jeffrey...

163
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:46,267
are we really going to end up
living like this?

164
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,767
Dad is gone,
and now mom is acting like this.

165
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:03,033
Jeff, you have
to be understanding.

166
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,900
Your dad abandoned her.
He's in Saudi Arabia.

167
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:10,033
Imagine she lost someone
she depended on all her life.

168
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,233
Have some sympathy.

169
00:09:12,367 --> 00:09:13,400
What are we going to do
with the clients

170
00:09:13,533 --> 00:09:15,067
who ordered sausages?

171
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,767
What if they come demanding it?

172
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:21,900
Godmother, our electricity and
water might get cut off, too.

173
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:25,500
We haven't paid the bill yet.

174
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,000
Perhaps you can help us pay
for our bills?

175
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:32,867
Oh no, Jeff...

176
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,933
I just paid my bills too.

177
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:37,767
I paid for water
and electricity bills.

178
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:41,067
Your uncle won't be sending
money till next week.

179
00:09:42,167 --> 00:09:44,467
I'm so sorry.

180
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,067
Thank you.

181
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,533
Be safe.

182
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:10,867
Benjo, can you give me a job?

183
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,733
Come on,
I really need the money.

184
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:16,600
Why? What do you need money for?

185
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:19,167
To pay for our electricity
and water bills.

186
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,067
Why do you have to worry
about that?

187
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,600
Where are your parents?

188
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:28,333
Come on, Benjo.

189
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:30,167
Please, let me do this job.

190
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:33,000
I can't. Stop pestering me.

191
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,800
You're too young for this job.

192
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,533
What if you get in an accident?

193
00:10:36,667 --> 00:10:38,133
Or if you accidentally hurt
someone else?

194
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:39,133
It will be my responsibility.

195
00:10:39,267 --> 00:10:40,200
Benjo, I promise...

196
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,733
- I'll be very careful...
- No, knock it off.

197
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:42,900
- I won't get in any accidents.
- No way.

198
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:44,067
- Please!
- I have to go.

199
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,567
- Benjo!
- Please. Knock it off.

200
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,167
Benjo!

201
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:49,200
Please!

202
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,233
He's right,
you're still a minor.

203
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:56,700
Ask your parents for help.

204
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,100
Wait! Wait!

205
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:08,333
- Wait!
- It's his fault!

206
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,333
- What seems to be the matter?
- He hit me with his car!

207
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:11,733
She scratched my car!

208
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:13,067
He ran me over!

209
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,767
- Wait a minute.
- He hit me with his car!

210
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:17,033
You cross the road
without looking!

211
00:11:17,167 --> 00:11:19,400
You want to run me over!

212
00:11:36,033 --> 00:11:37,633
<i> Jeff, Andrea!</i>

213
00:11:37,767 --> 00:11:38,967
<i> Jeff!</i>

214
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:43,167
It's your mom!

215
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:45,600
<i> Jeffrey.</i>

216
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:47,967
- What happened.
- Wait, wait, wait.

217
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:55,033
- Hello, is Felma inside?
- Yes, Ma'am. Come with me.

218
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:57,733
Okay, thank you, thank you.

219
00:11:57,867 --> 00:12:00,567
You're arguing with me
when you should be apologizing.

220
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,933
Why should I apologize?

221
00:12:02,633 --> 00:12:03,467
You know what...

222
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:06,967
if you can't be responsible
while on the road.

223
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:10,167
Stop roaming around
when you're drunk!

224
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,567
I'm not drunk!

225
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:12,733
Mom.

226
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:13,633
Dear.

227
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:18,833
Paz, why did
you bring them here?

228
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,100
Okay, let's fix this.

229
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:23,933
You should reconcile
with Mr. Salvador.

230
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:25,667
Pay for all the damages.

231
00:12:26,233 --> 00:12:27,633
Why should I pay him?

232
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:29,333
I'm the victim here.

233
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:30,633
Miss...

234
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:33,267
can you be responsible for once?

235
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,767
You made a violation.

236
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:35,933
You have to admit to it.

237
00:12:36,233 --> 00:12:37,167
And pay up.

238
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,933
I don't have the money
to pay you.

239
00:12:40,067 --> 00:12:43,700
Sir, how much
will the repair be?

240
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:46,333
- 20,000 pesos.
- Oh dear Lord!

241
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:48,433
I don't have that kind of money.

242
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,300
Don't let this guy fool you!

243
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:52,800
Why should we pay him?

244
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:54,500
- No way!
- You know what...

245
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,333
if you're not going to pay up.

246
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:59,600
I will sue you for the damages.

247
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,767
I will have you imprisoned.

248
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,333
Sir...

249
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:08,700
don't sue my mom.

250
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:10,733
We'll pay for the damages.

251
00:13:11,467 --> 00:13:13,200
We'll find a way to pay you.

252
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:15,100
Right, Godmother?

253
00:13:31,300 --> 00:13:34,600
<i>The number you have dialed
is now unattended.</i>

254
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:40,800
<i>The number you have dialed
is now unattended.</i>

255
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:48,133
Felma's not responding
to my calls and text messages.

256
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:49,933
I bet!

257
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:53,600
Your wife forbade her
from calling you.

258
00:13:54,433 --> 00:13:59,333
Why can't Hazel give your
family some consideration?

259
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:01,767
You know what, Bro,

260
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:07,667
you should talk to your wife
instead of leaving home.

261
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:09,367
How?

262
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:13,900
She wants me to cut
my connection with Felma.

263
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:18,367
Bro,

264
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,767
can you call Paz?

265
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:24,800
Tell her I want to talk
to Felma.

266
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:26,667
I just want to explain.

267
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:29,500
I want to tell her that I will
continue supporting them.

268
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:48,467
Miss Sonia.

269
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:50,933
Hey, Jeffrey.

270
00:14:51,067 --> 00:14:53,833
I haven't been seeing
your mom lately.

271
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,133
Does she have another supplier?

272
00:14:55,267 --> 00:14:58,267
No, my mom's been plagued
with problems lately.

273
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,433
We're broke.

274
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,233
Can I borrow some money
from you?

275
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:05,667
Oh my, I have already used
my money for supplies.

276
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:07,000
I'm so sorry.

277
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,833
Miss, how much for one kilo
of chicken?

278
00:15:10,967 --> 00:15:12,400
One hundred fifty.

279
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,400
Thief! My wallet!

280
00:15:20,533 --> 00:15:22,333
My wallet! Help! Thief!

281
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:24,200
He took my wallet!
Sir, please help me!

282
00:15:24,333 --> 00:15:25,933
- What's going on here?
- The kid took her wallet!

283
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:26,767
Catch him!

284
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:27,700
Hurry!

285
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:29,467
My wallet!

286
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:31,167
What?

287
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,000
Felma got summoned
to the Municipal Office?

288
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:36,533
Yes.

289
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:39,267
Hello, Paz.

290
00:15:40,333 --> 00:15:41,667
Why did Felma get summoned
to the Municipal Office?

291
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:44,500
She damaged someone's car.

292
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:45,633
You're wife...

293
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:48,800
Oh, sorry, I just remembered
she's not your wife.

294
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:50,500
Because she's drunk again!

295
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:51,833
Where are you?

296
00:15:52,367 --> 00:15:53,433
Are you with her?

297
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:58,033
No, I rushed home to get
my jewelry and have it pawned.

298
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,100
<i> To pawn jewelry?</i>

299
00:15:59,233 --> 00:15:59,833
Why?

300
00:16:00,133 --> 00:16:01,233
<i> The jewelry!</i>

301
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:03,200
Don't you get it, Manuel?

302
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:06,467
I need to pay the car owner.

303
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:10,000
Manuel, you should be
doing this.

304
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:15,367
If I don't pay the owner for the
damage, he will sue Felma!

305
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,167
Hey, boy.

306
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,467
I got tired of chasing you.

307
00:17:05,033 --> 00:17:06,033
Please, don't arrest me.

308
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:08,567
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
I'm sorry.

309
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,100
- Come on.
- I'm sorry.

310
00:17:10,233 --> 00:17:13,267
- Go with me to the precinct.
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

311
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,533
- Come on.
- I'm sorry.

312
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,433
- Bro.
- What?

313
00:17:19,567 --> 00:17:21,800
Do you have extra money?
Can you let me borrow some?

314
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:25,233
I do,

315
00:17:26,033 --> 00:17:28,567
it's payment for the
refrigerator that Paz bought.

316
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:30,900
But you can have it for now.

317
00:17:31,033 --> 00:17:35,367
There! Thanks, Bro, I will pay
you back once I get my salary.

318
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:38,433
I need to send money to Felma.

319
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:43,133
It's all my fault.

320
00:17:43,933 --> 00:17:45,233
My life wouldn't be
this complicated

321
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:46,933
if I hadn't left my children.

322
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,400
Sir, so you don't want
to reconcile with her?

323
00:18:05,533 --> 00:18:07,033
You wanted payment?

324
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:07,833
Yes.

325
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:14,767
Hello?

326
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:17,733
Miss Felma Cruz?

327
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:19,867
Who's this?

328
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:21,867
I'm calling from the precinct.

329
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,067
<i> Is Jeffrey Cruz your son?</i>

330
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:26,033
What happened to my son?

331
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:28,133
<i> He's here at the precinct.</i>

332
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:30,867
<i>There's a theft complaint
against him.</i>

333
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:31,700
What?

334
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:35,067
Okay, I'll be on my way.

335
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:37,867
Ma'am, where are you going?

336
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,367
To the precinct!
My son needs me!

337
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:41,600
You're leaving?

338
00:18:41,733 --> 00:18:43,567
You haven't paid
for the damages yet!

339
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:45,200
Can we settle this later?

340
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,733
My son needs me!

341
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:48,900
He is being accused
of stealing.

342
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:52,300
He needs me! Is that hard
to understand?

343
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,233
- Is your mom coming?
- Calm down.

344
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:11,467
Ma'am!

345
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:13,133
- That's enough.
- Looks like she abandoned you!

346
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:15,100
She doesn't discipline you!

347
00:19:15,233 --> 00:19:16,667
Don't hurt my son!

348
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:19,800
I will have you put in jail!
I will do it!

349
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:23,200
So you're this thief's mother?

350
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,567
My son is not a thief!

351
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:27,033
Why are you accusing him
of stealing?

352
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:27,967
Look at this!

353
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:30,033
He stole this from me!

354
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:33,967
She's telling the truth,
Mrs. Cruz.

355
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:35,867
We caught him stealing.

356
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:41,000
Jeffrey, dear,
did you steal from that woman?

357
00:19:41,733 --> 00:19:43,067
I did!

358
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:47,667
- See?
- Mrs. Tuazon, please calm down.

359
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:50,333
Why did you do that?

360
00:19:51,367 --> 00:19:53,467
To get us some money.

361
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:58,033
To pay the car owner
for the damage repair.

362
00:19:58,867 --> 00:20:00,100
I don't want you
to go to jail.

363
00:20:00,233 --> 00:20:02,033
I can't let that happen!

364
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:05,033
You shouldn't have done that!
It's wrong, son.

365
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,500
It's a grave sin!

366
00:20:06,633 --> 00:20:09,567
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

367
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:10,800
You shouldn't apologize to me.

368
00:20:10,933 --> 00:20:12,167
Tell her you're sorry.

369
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:15,433
Hey! I won't let it slide
with a simple apology!

370
00:20:15,567 --> 00:20:19,733
He needs to learn his lesson.
He needs to rot in jail.

371
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:21,800
<i>He has to pay
for what he did!</i>

372
00:20:22,533 --> 00:20:25,033
Miss, he's just a boy.

373
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,367
You can't put a minor
in jail, can you?

374
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,767
It depends on whether
Mrs. Tuazon went ahead

375
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,000
with her complaints.

376
00:20:31,133 --> 00:20:34,667
We will have to turn him
over to the DSWD for custody.

377
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:35,933
You're taking him away from me?

378
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:37,600
You're taking my son?

379
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:39,033
To get him rehabbed.

380
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:40,500
So he won't commit
a crime again.

381
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:43,067
Mom, I don't want that
to happen.

382
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,033
Don't let them take me, Mom.

383
00:20:45,167 --> 00:20:47,900
I don't want to be away
from you.

384
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:06,800
He canceled my call.

385
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:11,967
Friend, let him cool off
for now.

386
00:21:12,333 --> 00:21:14,567
It's not as if he can go home
to Felma.

387
00:21:15,467 --> 00:21:17,733
Your husband isn't going
anywhere.

388
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:20,400
Well, you're right.

389
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,100
He'll come around.

390
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,667
He has nowhere else to go.

391
00:21:30,633 --> 00:21:33,367
He'll be back to me for sure.

392
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:38,700
Mom, I don't want to be away
from you.

393
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:41,433
Mom, don't let them do that.
Mom, please.

394
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,233
I don't want to be away
from you!

395
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:45,967
I'm begging you, please help me!

396
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:50,967
Ma'am, you got your money back.

397
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:53,800
Can you let my son go?

398
00:21:53,933 --> 00:21:56,167
<i>That's why your son grew up
to be a criminal!</i>

399
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:58,000
Because you're an enabler!

400
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:00,267
My son is not a criminal!

401
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:03,167
I raised them well!

402
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,533
<i>Please don't judge us that way.</i>

403
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,933
This is the first time
he has ever done this.

404
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:12,300
Our family is going through
a lot right now.

405
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:14,600
That is the only reason
why he did this.

406
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:17,033
That's not an excuse to steal!

407
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,933
That's why I'm asking you
to forgive my son.

408
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,233
I'm so sorry, Miss Tuazon.

409
00:22:25,667 --> 00:22:26,733
Don't be mad at me!

410
00:22:26,867 --> 00:22:29,467
Don't take me away from my mom,
I'm begging you.

411
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:32,000
Don't take me away from my mom.

412
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,933
Can you forgive him?

413
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:39,500
He's begging for
your forgiveness.

414
00:22:40,367 --> 00:22:41,567
And who are you?

415
00:22:44,867 --> 00:22:45,967
I'm a friend.

416
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,833
Mrs. Tuazon, we all make
mistakes sometimes.

417
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,700
We all go through tough times.

418
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:57,100
That's why we sometimes do
things we don't want to do.

419
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:59,600
That's probably what happened
to...

420
00:22:59,733 --> 00:23:01,567
- Jeffrey.
- Jeffrey.

421
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:03,233
He didn't want to steal
from you.

422
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:05,300
He's desperate to help
his mom...

423
00:23:06,700 --> 00:23:07,800
that's why he did it.

424
00:23:07,933 --> 00:23:08,867
You have a mom, too, don't you?

425
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,133
Of course!

426
00:23:10,267 --> 00:23:11,800
I'm a good daughter.

427
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:15,033
I will do everything
for my mom.

428
00:23:15,167 --> 00:23:16,700
So you understand
what I'm trying to say?

429
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:20,867
Jeffrey did everything
he could for his mom.

430
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,333
I hope you can forgive him.

431
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,367
Please don't file a complaint
against him.

432
00:23:30,933 --> 00:23:32,800
Thank you so much,
Mr. Salvador.

433
00:23:32,933 --> 00:23:37,200
If you didn't help us, they
probably took my son away.

434
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:39,833
You're welcome.

435
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:41,767
By the way,

436
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:43,567
where's Jeffrey?

437
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:45,500
I can give you a ride home.

438
00:23:47,067 --> 00:23:49,233
No, thank you, we don't want
to bother you.

439
00:23:49,633 --> 00:23:52,800
I asked him to get a cab.

440
00:23:56,067 --> 00:23:57,967
I'm sorry about your car.

441
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:01,967
Don't worry, I'll find a way
to pay you for the damage.

442
00:24:04,567 --> 00:24:05,733
You don't need to do that,
Felma.

443
00:24:07,233 --> 00:24:08,367
Can I call you Felma?

444
00:24:11,933 --> 00:24:12,867
I understand you.

445
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:15,133
Just like Jeffrey,

446
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:18,033
you've done something
you didn't want to do.

447
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,233
Just be careful next time.

448
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:26,033
Does that mean
you're not going to sue me?

449
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,267
No, I won't.

450
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:30,500
Thank you.

451
00:24:31,267 --> 00:24:33,167
Thank you so much, Mr. Salvador.

452
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:37,400
You helped us out a lot.

453
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,067
Noah.

454
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,333
Just call me Noah.

455
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:04,300
She's so pretty, Hazel.

456
00:25:04,433 --> 00:25:06,700
I'm sorry if I left you.

457
00:25:06,833 --> 00:25:08,067
I'm sorry too.

458
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:10,300
I will help you take care
of Jessica.

459
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:11,767
Let's start over.

460
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:13,700
This will be the last time
I'll talk to you.

461
00:25:13,833 --> 00:25:15,400
Don't call us anymore.

462
00:25:15,533 --> 00:25:17,067
Don't send us a letter.

463
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:21,000
And you don't need to send us
money or anything.

464
00:25:21,367 --> 00:25:24,500
I can't bear to lose you, Felma.

465
00:25:25,133 --> 00:25:27,533
I can no longer return
that love.

466
00:25:27,667 --> 00:25:30,200
We can survive without you.

467
00:25:30,433 --> 00:25:34,100
Thank you for all the years
you had with us.

468
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:37,200
But, Mom, I will miss my dad.

469
00:25:37,367 --> 00:25:39,400
I will provide for you, dear.

470
00:25:39,533 --> 00:25:41,700
What happens when you
get tired again?

471
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:43,733
I will help her out.

472
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:45,800
And you can help her, too.

473
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:47,333
Right, Mom?
We can get through this.

474
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:49,367
As long as you're with me.

475
00:25:49,633 --> 00:25:51,233
I will endure anything.

476
00:25:51,367 --> 00:25:52,600
I promise.
